# PAGE HOME
# ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
page.home=Home
page.home.title=Html yoda presentation experience
page.home.text=<p>Hype is an online tool that help you to build your HTML presentations with Reveal.js</p><p>You can easy create a presentation with a unique step form, and start to work on it with a JSFiddle like workspace.</p><p>Data are yours, they are saved on your Github account as a Gist. And you know what ? Gist are versionned !</p><p>During a presentation, share your slides and take control of it. You are the only person who can navigate into slides ! Or if you want, you can use your smartphone as a remote !</br>All this is possible with the technology of webscoket.</p><br/><p><a class="btn btn-primary btn-large" href="/authenticate/github">Login !</a></p>
page.home.col1.title=Your workspace
page.home.col1.text=<div class="row-fluid"><p>Create and update your presentations directly online with a JSFiddle like workspace</p><p>On the left, you have the HTML & CSS code. On the other side, the preview of your code !<br/>This preview is made in realtime, no need to refresh the page or to click on a 'run' button</p><p>To save your modification, simply press "CTRL + S" as usual (if there are some feedback, I will implement a VIM editor !)</p></div><br/><div class="row-fluid"><img src="/assets/images/workspace.png" /></div>
page.home.col2.title=Technical stack
page.home.col2.text=<div class="row-fluid"><div class="span4"><img src="/assets/images/angular.jpeg" /><a href="http://www.angularjs.org" title="angular.js">AngularJS</a> is used for all the front-end interface (single page application), so as for ajax call to Github's API.</div><div class="span4"><img src="/assets/images/play.png" /><a href="http://www.playframework.com" title="Play! framework">Play! framework 2.1</a> deliver all file and it's use for i18n, authentification and websocket.</div><div class="span4"><img src="/assets/images/github.png" /><a href="http://github.com">Github</a> is used like a datastore with version. Moreover it's a login service.</div></div>

